<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,853,1021]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Coninck" authorityYear="1965" box="[189,395,853,879]" class="Adenophorea" family="Comesomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Nematoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dorylaimopsinae">Dorylaimopsinae</taxonomicName>
. Cuticle with lateral differentiation of irregularly-spaced larger dots, sometimes arranged in transverse rows; posterior portion of buccal cavity cylindrical, with three thorn-like teeth at border to anterior portion (except in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hope &amp; Zhang, 1995" authorityName="Hope &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[619,1056,924,951]" class="Adenophorea" family="Comesomatidae" genus="Hopperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="hexadentata">
<emphasis box="[619,798,924,950]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. hexadentata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hope W. D. &amp; Zhang Z." box="[806,1056,924,951]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="119 - 138" refId="ref14431" refString="Hope W. D. &amp; Zhang Z. 1995. New nematodes fom the Yellow sea, Hopperia hexadentata n. sp. and Cervonema deltensis n. sp. (Chromadorida: Comesomatidae), with observations on morphology and systematics. Invertebrate Biology 114: 119 - 138." type="journal article" year="1995">Hope &amp; Zhang, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which has six teeth); ovaries usually outstretched, reflexed ovaries sometimes present; spicules arcuate; gubernaculum with caudal or dorso-caudal apophyses.
</paragraph>
